This game is not finished, no doubt about it. Was there ever though? TaleWorlds said time and time again, the game isn't finished and that it's early access. The negative reviews in here critisizing it for not being finished yet are cringy as ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•. No ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• sherlock.Here's an actually useful review: If you liked Mount & Blade: Warband, you WILL probably enjoy the game already in its current state. The bugs are there for sure, but I don't feel like they ruin the gameplay by any stretch. To me, the most noticeable early access thing are some minor graphical bugs here and there, performance issues and a lack of content. Mind you, it already has more content then Mount & Blade: Warband, but it is far from finished.I'm not trying to be one of those fanboys who claims the game is perfect. It is NOT FINISHED as I have said many times now. But the negative reviews in here are not fair, and as I said, cringe as ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•. If you don't like playing early access games, just wait till it is fully released you fat obnoxious fecal consumer. Love you TaleWorlds, amazing game!

This was an epic experience. I have a lot to talk about so I will dive right into it.First of all, the game looks great. Love the artstyle of Borderlands!The music is AMAZING by Jesper Kyd (Dude who did AC II's music etc, and just so happens to be my countryman).The gameplay and gunplay is way more fun then in Borderlands 2 in my opinion which is of course a great thing! As opposed to some people in here I thought the story was pretty good, but BUTSPOILER ALERT! SPOILER ALERT! SPOILER ALERT!Two things:One, Maya's death was a waste. Considering she was the siren class in Borderlands 2 and a very cool character, they killed her off way too early in the game, and the death scene was not even that great.Secondly Ava is just a straight up dislikable character. You can't change my mind.Minor complaint: Lilith I have a name, stop calling me "killer".Enough complaining, this game is great. Great music, great atmosphere, good old Borderlands humor, good gameplay, nice story. A must have in modern gaming! I would recommend it, even at full price.

I have not play this game as much as some people have, but I mean.... I can still review it, right? Right?So, first of all. I never played the first Borderlands, so this is my entrance to the franchise. The graphic style was a liiiiiittle off-putting to me initially, but as time would have it, now I find it f*cking awesome!The story is cool, with good writing and it has some very interesting characters. Borderlands 2 (as well as the franchise in general) is a game very much focused on humor in terms of dialogue and general presentation. It is a loot-based shooter RPG game, that is great to play singleplayer, but really shines through playing it coop with friends.TL;DR - Charming graphics, cool story and characters. Loot-based shooter RPG you can play with your friends.A modern gaming classic.

First of all, this game has some compatibility issues for PC (Disappearing carriages etc). You must install the software RivarTuner Statistics Server, and allow the file AC3SP to run through it (found in Steam/steamapps/common etc). Remember to set it to 60 FPS, even if your screen can handle more.The game is great! Love the setting. I for one also like Connor (badass native American assasssin). I don't get the hate for him. Sure, he's not Ezio, but he's badass.The story is pretty good, the game looks great for its age, and the combat animations are badass.All in all, I'd recommend this game. I give it 7/10, one of the better AC games.

This game is only worth playing if you're a huge fan of AC (like me). The plot is fine, and Altair is a badass character. But as a game, it is really not that enjoyable. The missions are tedious and way too similar, combat and movement mechanics are wanky... Graphically, the game looks great for its age. In short: Play it for the story, once. In my opinion, it has zero replayability. The AC franchise truly began to shine in AC II.

The game itself is good. However, there are many issues that make it impossible to recommend. 1. The game forces you to download all of its 50-60GB through a 3rd party launcher, meaning that download time counts towards playtime. This means that you can't get a refund through Steam since you've most likely passed the 2-hour mark. 2. It's a torrent download. Ew.3. The Lieutenant, Sergeant, and Major packs are a scam. At the moment, there is no way to activate them. The website to activate your items has been down since release.4. The servers go down pretty often and yesterday many people, including me, were experiencing matchmaking issues making us unable to play.Now, what about the actual game?It's decent. Gameplay is pretty fun, it looks nice and there's a decent amount of customization as well. However, the game does have its own issues. - The progression is extremely slow. It has become your standard grindy F2P game. - Even though I meet the recommended requirements, performance in normal battles hasn't been great. It barely runs at 60 FPS (usually in the high 50s, low 60s) on lowest settings. Performance gets a lot better in TDM where I easily get over 100 FPS, but it still doesn't feel "fluid". I can't really explain it, but it feels like the game is running at 60 Hz even though I have a 144 Hz monitor (I could be wrong here, my brain could just be deceiving me).- The spawns in TDM are terrible, a lot of the time you spawn in front of an enemy with no spawn protection essentially becming a free kill.I wanted to like this game, I really did, but in it's current state it's pretty hard to recommend.

This game is like how Battlefield 2042 turned out. Hot Pursuit 2 is my favourite of all the NFS series so I had high hopes for it when they released another Hot Pursuit game.. Holy crap I was soo wrong! Everything about it is awful but the handling.. I can't even.. So for them to make decent previous NFS games then come out with this hot turd reminds me how Battlefield 2042 turned out.. except they had decided to keep the handling and use it for the next set of NFS games. I weep for the Battlefield franchise..

Well besides the fact they had gotten rid of the core parts of Battlefield.. after a month of its release & the many patches.. this game still has major flaws.. even if the game was free it's not worth your bandwidth. Soo many little issues and soo many big issues.* The maps are far too big* The vehicles.. it's all vehicles..* The specialists.. well lets just say they're wrong to put into this game but all them have glitches & issues* Spawn locations are insanely stupid. Your either soo far away, directly in firing range, directly in front of an enemy vehicle so you get run over like its GTA Online or bombed by a helicopter* Majority of the maps are just.. terrible.. and there is only 7 maps.. 7..* The guns are still very unbalanced.. there's only 22 of them* Vehicles are still incredibly overpowered & dominant in 2042* No campaign, didn't bother me till I realised where is my money going? funding Dice's secret terrorist hobby? sounds like it cause I'm not seeing any value in this game*UI hasn't been fixed or updated.. *Still no server browserAll in all it's just lacking so much content & it's still wildly unbalanced. They have taken the 'Porsche' approach, pay a lot more for less..

This is a game for those who..- Want more action then all the Die Hard movies combined & more community appraisal then Downton Abbey- Do not attend a seminar on how to improve your little hermit life or on how to get rich by saying Yes (Hookers can be rather dirty.. your father should have educated you on this..)- Do not find there not so distant cousin attractive when slamming a few beers at a BBQ.. okay I'll let this one slide for some of youThis game will buy you drinks at a fancy club, laugh at your jokes, escort you back to it's place & even pay for that sketchy Uber to take you home the next morning.. meanwhile you'll slowly realise you were hard brain penetrated in the cerebral cortex by it. It's a ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• Win-Win imo.. It's either this or some smutty retarded semi-hentai game on Steam.

I thought the Assassin's Creed series was the laziest contribution by Ubisoft.. Turns out It was the Crew 2. - No new plot (cause there isn't any)- No new cars (as far as i can tell its at best.. 2 to 4)- All vehicles end up feeling the same- Exhausting dialogue that can't be droned out- Music that felt like it was chosen by Ministry of Sound (all so repetitive & fairly dated)- Civilian vehicles loading in & out randomly - Horrible driving physics with the so-called weather changes- Still an absolute bi*** when it comes to vehicle upgrades since the only way to get upgrades is by grinding away till your fingers & thumbs becomes as stumpy as a fat ginger on a mobility scooter- Can barely see when racing across the states at night timeHowever.. If I have to say something positive to.. balance this out it would be..- Money is very easily obtained as you progress so vehicle purchases aren't as painful as your best mate dating your ex.- Your soul can still be on the Ubi-Slack-Market by doing the microtransactions- Your balloon knot virginity will be nicely lubed & ready to go by the developers if you purchase the Gold EditionEnjoy..

The game is amazing and i'm in love with it! It puts you in the adrenaline all the time. It makes you feel inside a medieval battlefield. It's bloody, gross and messy... it's just perfect. Train the combos and the moves. Adapt yourself to the weapon that suits you better. There are plenty of skins to custom your character (but true chads play 1st person POV amirite?). Last but not least, give your warcry and have fun!UE4 does it's job, nothing fancy, max settings seem light, DLSS for lower end systems, and a very stable DX12 version wich is rare on UE4 tittles these days.So yeah, i'm addicted, and i kinda feel like i have been missing out on Mordhau (this is my 1st game of this kind, ever), but now i'm here to stay!Oh, and ofc... Epic Game Store sucks and Steam is life

For and against     Pros   Cons     It's possible to save online game, which also helps fight against gliches   Some bugs may appear     Interesting design combined - game is hd seeing by the hud, while sprites are mostly stretched to make it look pixely   Only a few servers     Nice variety of characters and possibility to choose game style   Only 2 difficulties which basicaly vary like this - very easy, very hard     Interesting way how game works, it's like a turn based, but not really, because you can move in realtime, while various effects, clichesm monsters will only trigger upon activating doors or initialising a special trigger   Loadout gives stats, but no visual effects are applied, an example, if you have a nice sword, you'll still see your default stick no matter what     Easy and entertaining way to get rid of some time   Game goal is pretty mainstream - you just have to get out or stay as long as you can, that's all, which might make this game boring after a while     Integrated with Steam (achievements, cloud, trading cards, maybe more)   It's easy to die, because game doesn't ever warn you about your current status, you just have to keep watching that status bar     It's still being worked on, so there might be more features in the future and the community is active aswell, so it's not a dead end, hopefully :)   Doubt that it's worth the money, but you could wait for an off-sale   I could probably keep going forever... One of the best horror games I've ever played, and that's saying something when the game is originally made on the HL1 engine and is completely free! A psychological horror game that takes you for a ride with a well crafted story, lots of scary moments and well designed monsters that all have relevance to the main character. Unlockables, different endings, developer commentary and different gamemodes all add to the replayability of the game too. All in all, it's great! If you're a fan of (psychological) horror, you won't regret playing it!Pros:> Good, well crafted story.> Awesome soundtrack.> Very well designed monsters.> Lots of genuinely scary moments.> Even with guns, you never feel completely safe.> Lots of replayablity (multiple endings, unlockables, custom maps etc.).> Good boss fights.> Stamina, health and healing mechanics don't feel too OP.> Great level design.> Fantastic atmosphere throughout the game.> One of those games you'll never forget.Cons:> Kind of old engine, performance issues can arise (especially when playing for long sessions).> Layout of the map/objectives may be confusing when playing for the first time.> Places that are meant to give hints to the player aren't very obvious, which adds to the point mentioned above.> Small inventory, and the issues that come with that.Verdict: 10/10SCP-035's chainsaw weilding older brother can keep that doorknob!

This game barely makes any sense whatsoever, and that's what's amazing about it!So the general idea is that you prevent a bomb from exploding and killing you all. And McPixel fixes this in the weirdest way possible. Shove it in someones ass (yep, it happens a lot more then you think), put a bucket over it or sometimes actually defusing it. But as there is only 1 way to prevent the explosion, there a millions of ways to fail. These fails are often more hilarious then the actual solving of the puzzle and if you find all the fails you'll get a gold plate on the level! It doesn't really do anything, but it's there, All in all, fantastic little game!PROS:- Easy gameplay- No logic, pure chaos- 'funny' jokes and situations (depends on your tase of humor af course)- Lots of references to other games- Amazing soundtrack- MCPIXEL!!!!!CONS:- Not being able to find the solution will result in frustration and spam clicking everywhere- Little to no replay value after you reach gold on every level

Great game! This game was actually the first game I bought on steam. But that aside, this is a nice game! The best part about it in my opinion is the fact is has 3 campaigns: Marine, Alien (Xenomorph) and Predator. Let's start off with the marine campaign:In the Marine campaign you play as Rookie (what a surprise) who's squad is killed in a Xenomorph ambush. Basicly, you're on your own for the biggest part of the campaign. You will find other marines from time to time, but they usually don't last very long. It is a funny campaign since you have 3 'boss fights' in it: The Xenomorph Queen (ironicly the first and easiest one), the battle with the Predator and the battle with Wayland. There are some different weapons you can choose but for the most part it's a general FPS with the addition of aliens and the motion tracker.In the Alien campaign you play as Specimen 6, one of the colony's guinea pig Xenomorphs. Unlike the 2001 version of this game, you start immediately as a fully grown Xenomorph. Your goal is to break out and kill humans, and eventually predators. Very cool campaign, unfortunately it's the smallest one. The fact you can walk on any surface is also nice, and the stealth kills and finishing moves are both amazing and gory. Be aware of the androids btw, they're very dangerous...Finally in the Predator campaign you have to hunt down the Abomination (it's basicly a Predalien). To do this, the Predator has an awesome variaty of weapons at it's disposal. The plasma rifle is overpowered, the mines are too, the smart disk can be difficult to handle with fast moving targets and the spear as well. The cloacking, stealth and the different visions really add to the feeling of the predator campaign. Once again the stealth kills and finishing moves are both amazing and gory.There's also a multiplayer in the game with many gamemodes that barely anyone plays. Seriously, 95% of the games are Team Deathmatch or Mixed Team Deathmatch. They are fun, don't get me wrong, but it can be repetative to do the whole time. Also by playing matches you can level up and unlock new skins for your Marine, Alien or Predator.All in all, very good game, nice graphics and lovely 3 different campaigns. Get this game if you enjoy the different play styles it offers or if you just love the Alien and Predator universe! :)P.S. I haven't really seen anyone play the DLC maps, so I don't know why they're there :P

However, now that Emperor Edition is out, most if not all the nasty bugs and glitches are gone. If you want to change various things in the game you specificly don't like, the community got you covered. There's a huge amount of mods out there to create the total war you like to play. Or just play the vanilla version :P  Anyway, the historical accuracy (or authenticity, right Ella ;P) is good, the battles are intense and Rome is mother to us all! (sorry, had to do that :P)P.S. A slight dislike is the price. Not only for the game, but also for the DLC's. None of the DLC's are 'must haves' in my opinion, so if you don't have enouch money for the game I suggest you wait for a sale on steam. Also, make sure your computer can handle this game!

This is one amazing shooter game that any fan of RO2 would love. It is different than RO2, but by its core its still pretty much the same game. This game is more fast phase than RO2.For the people who are not familiar with RO2 let me explain this game a bit.Its a FPS shooter game that takes place in Vietnam during the Vietnam war.In this game you have 3 different time periods: early, mid and late war. Each period provides different weapons, armies and support.North Vietnam has a choice between 2 armies while South Vietnam has 4 (in late war only 1). Each army will provide you with different weapons.There are also different roles between both factions, but at its roots they are almost the same. Like one has RPG and other has grenadier. If you are new then don't go as the commander and squad leader. You cant take commander role unless you have hit the level requirements, but still leave it for a bit more experienced players since you can win a lot easier with a good commander. Just watch and learn until you feel ready enough to try out. Squad leaders are just a mobile spawn point units for South Vietnam while for North Vietnam they make tunnels (spawn points). If you are good at not dying be sure to go as the squad leader.This game combines tactics with fun very well. It is semi realistic. Similar to RO2 each hit can be super deadly, but in this game getting killed from 1 shot is not as often. I strongly suggest this game to any FPS tactical game fan.
